# Netlify _redirects — first match wins, top-to-bottom.
#
# Equipment-hub install routes (2026-05-06 PWA install hotfix). Serve the
# equipment HTML — same React app, different <link rel="manifest"> — so iOS
# Safari / Android Chrome read start_url=/equipment at HTML parse time,
# before any JS runs. The dynamic in-React applyManifestHref() helper stays
# as defensive runtime sync but is NOT relied on for install. /fueling* is
# the legacy alias and gets the same treatment for operators with old
# bookmarks who tap Add to Home Screen.
/equipment       /equipment.html  200
/equipment/*     /equipment.html  200
/fueling         /equipment.html  200
/fueling/*       /equipment.html  200

# SPA fallback — any other unmatched path serves index.html so client-side
# routing (React Router) can take over. Status 200 (not 301) so the browser
# URL stays as-is. MUST stay last; it's the catch-all.
/*  /index.html  200
